LINE.Text: The Internet of Things, or loT for short, is a simple concept that covers an increasingly complex
application: everything is connected to the Internet. Whether it's a robotic manufacturing device,
a soda machine at the mall, the guidance system in your car, the appliances in your house or the
Google glasses on your face, virtually everything will be talking to each other. Except perhaps the
actual humans. And it's all happening right now, all around us.
Most of us will interact with the loT right at home. The smart home, that is. A smart,
or connected, home leverages solutions from companies like Control4 to get all the
different devices and systems in a home talking to one another-and you-while also
providing one-touch control from virtually any mobile device.
